{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1359,"text":"Our ability to create\nand sustain economic growth"},{"time":6480,"text":"is the defining challenge of our time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9240,"text":"Of course there are other challenges --"},{"time":11800,"text":"health care, disease burdens\nand pandemics,"},{"time":14960,"text":"environmental challenges"},{"time":17400,"text":"and, of course, radicalized terrorism."},{"time":20800,"text":"However,"},{"time":22040,"text":"to the extent that we can actually\nsolve the economic growth challenge,"},{"time":26640,"text":"it will take us a long way"},{"time":28000,"text":"to solving the challenges\nthat I've just elucidated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31400,"text":"More importantly,"},{"time":33080,"text":"unless and until we solve economic growth"},{"time":37600,"text":"and create sustainable,\nlong-term economic growth,"},{"time":41640,"text":"we'll be unable to address"},{"time":44080,"text":"the seemingly intractable challenges\nthat continue to pervade the globe today,"},{"time":49440,"text":"whether it's health care,\neducation or economic development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54680,"text":"The fundamental question is this:"},{"time":57520,"text":"How are we going to create economic growth"},{"time":60160,"text":"in advanced and developed economies\nlike the United States and across Europe"},{"time":64760,"text":"at a time when they continue to struggle"},{"time":66840,"text":"to create economic growth\nafter the financial crisis?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70480,"text":"They continue to underperform"},{"time":73280,"text":"and to see an erosion in the three\nkey drivers of economic growth:"},{"time":78040,"text":"capital, labor and productivity."},{"time":82120,"text":"In particular,"},{"time":83600,"text":"these developed economies\ncontinue to see debts and deficits,"},{"time":88560,"text":"the decline and erosion\nof both the quality and quantity of labor"},{"time":93440,"text":"and they also see productivity stalling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96600,"text":"In a similar vein,"},{"time":98320,"text":"how are we going to create\neconomic growth in the emerging markets,"},{"time":101760,"text":"where 90 percent\nof the world's population lives"},{"time":105040,"text":"and where, on average,"},{"time":106600,"text":"70 percent of the population\nis under the age of 25?"},{"time":110640,"text":"In these countries,"},{"time":112120,"text":"it is essential that they grow\nat a minimum of seven percent a year"},{"time":116320,"text":"in order to put a dent in poverty"},{"time":118440,"text":"and to double per capita incomes\nin one generation."},{"time":122520,"text":"And yet today,"},{"time":124600,"text":"the largest emerging economies --"},{"time":126720,"text":"countries with at least\n50 million people --"},{"time":129440,"text":"continue to struggle to reach\nthat seven percent magic mark."},{"time":133760,"text":"Worse than that,"},{"time":135000,"text":"countries like India, Russia,\nSouth Africa, Brazil and even China"},{"time":139640,"text":"are falling below\nthat seven percent number"},{"time":142160,"text":"and, in many cases, actually regressing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145800,"text":"Economic growth matters."},{"time":148440,"text":"With economic growth,"},{"time":149920,"text":"countries and societies\nenter into a virtuous cycle"},{"time":154120,"text":"of upward mobility, opportunity\nand improved living standards."},{"time":159240,"text":"Without growth,\ncountries contract and atrophy,"},{"time":163080,"text":"not just in the annals\nof economic statistics"},{"time":166320,"text":"but also in the meaning of life\nand how lives are lived."},{"time":170600,"text":"Economic growth matters\npowerfully for the individual."},{"time":175120,"text":"If growth wanes,"},{"time":176760,"text":"the risk to human progress"},{"time":178800,"text":"and the risk of political\nand social instability rises,"},{"time":183240,"text":"and societies become dimmer,\ncoarser and smaller."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188600,"text":"The context matters."},{"time":190320,"text":"And countries in emerging markets"},{"time":191960,"text":"do not need to grow at the same\nrates as developed countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197240,"text":"Now, I know some of you in this room\nfind this to be a risky proposition."},{"time":202680,"text":"There are some people here"},{"time":204560,"text":"who will turn around\nand be quite disillusioned"},{"time":207120,"text":"by what's happened around the world"},{"time":208920,"text":"and basically ascribe that\nto economic growth."},{"time":212240,"text":"You worry about the\noverpopulation of the planet."},{"time":215760,"text":"And looking at the UN's\nrecent statistics and projections"},{"time":218680,"text":"that the world will have\n11 billion people on the planet"},{"time":221400,"text":"before it plateaus in 2100,"},{"time":224000,"text":"you're concerned about what that does\nto natural resources --"},{"time":227840,"text":"arable land, potable water,\nenergy and minerals."},{"time":232800,"text":"You are also concerned about\nthe degradation of the environment."},{"time":236760,"text":"And you worry about how man,"},{"time":239920,"text":"embodied in the corporate globalist,"},{"time":242560,"text":"has become greedy and corrupt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246560,"text":"But I'm here to tell you today\nthat economic growth"},{"time":249960,"text":"has been the backbone\nof changes in living standards"},{"time":253360,"text":"of millions of people around the world."},{"time":255960,"text":"And more importantly,"},{"time":257800,"text":"it's not just economic growth\nthat has been driven by capitalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264280,"text":"The definition of capitalism,\nvery simply put,"},{"time":267760,"text":"is that the factors of production,"},{"time":269840,"text":"such as trade and industry,\ncapital and labor,"},{"time":273240,"text":"are left in the hands\nof the private sector and not the state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277680,"text":"It's really essential here\nthat we understand"},{"time":280440,"text":"that fundamentally the critique\nis not for economic growth per se"},{"time":285480,"text":"but what has happened to capitalism."},{"time":287560,"text":"And to the extent that we need to create\neconomic growth over the long term,"},{"time":291600,"text":"we're going to have to pursue it\nwith a better form of economic stance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297320,"text":"Economic growth needs capitalism,"},{"time":300240,"text":"but it needs it to work properly."},{"time":302840,"text":"And as I mentioned a moment ago,"},{"time":305160,"text":"the core of the capitalist system\nhas been defined by private actors."},{"time":311720,"text":"And even this, however,\nis a very simplistic dichotomy."},{"time":315800,"text":"Capitalism: good; non-capitalism: bad."},{"time":319120,"text":"When in practical experience,"},{"time":321800,"text":"capitalism is much more of a spectrum."},{"time":324280,"text":"And we have countries such as China,"},{"time":326560,"text":"which have practiced\nmore state capitalism,"},{"time":329000,"text":"and we have countries\nlike the Unites States"},{"time":331120,"text":"which are more market capitalist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333160,"text":"Our efforts to critique\nthe capitalist system, however,"},{"time":336320,"text":"have tended to focus\non countries like China"},{"time":339560,"text":"that are in fact\nnot blatantly market capitalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343600,"text":"However, there is\na real reason and real concern"},{"time":347280,"text":"for us to now focus our attentions\non purer forms of capitalism,"},{"time":351960,"text":"particularly those embodied\nby the United States."},{"time":355280,"text":"This is really important"},{"time":357080,"text":"because this type of capitalism"},{"time":359560,"text":"has increasingly\nbeen afforded the critique"},{"time":362840,"text":"that it is now fostering corruption"},{"time":365280,"text":"and, worse still,"},{"time":366680,"text":"it's increasing income inequality --"},{"time":370120,"text":"the idea that the few are benefiting\nat the expense of the many."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376760,"text":"The two really critical questions\nthat we need to address"},{"time":380000,"text":"is how can we fix capitalism"},{"time":382720,"text":"so that it can help create economic growth"},{"time":385520,"text":"but at the same time\ncan help to address social ills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389720,"text":"In order to think about that framing,\nwe have to ask ourselves,"},{"time":393120,"text":"how does capitalism work today?"},{"time":395760,"text":"Very simplistically,"},{"time":397960,"text":"capitalism is set on the basis\nof an individual utility maximizer --"},{"time":403760,"text":"a selfish individual\nwho goes after what he or she wants."},{"time":408080,"text":"And only after they've\nmaximized their utility"},{"time":411240,"text":"do they then decide it's important"},{"time":413760,"text":"to provide support\nto other social contracts."},{"time":417360,"text":"Of course, in this system\ngovernments do tax,"},{"time":420800,"text":"and they use part of their revenues\nto fund social programs,"},{"time":424560,"text":"recognizing that government's role\nis not just regulation"},{"time":427440,"text":"but also to be arbiter of social goods."},{"time":431320,"text":"But nevertheless,"},{"time":432640,"text":"this framework --"},{"time":434000,"text":"this two-stage framework --"},{"time":436000,"text":"is the basis from which we must now start"},{"time":438000,"text":"to think about how we can\nimprove the capitalist model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441520,"text":"I would argue that there are\ntwo sides to this challenge."},{"time":445520,"text":"First of all,"},{"time":446760,"text":"we can draw on the right-wing policies"},{"time":449720,"text":"to see what could be beneficial for us"},{"time":451600,"text":"to think about how\nwe can improve capitalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454440,"text":"In particular,"},{"time":455720,"text":"right-leaning policies"},{"time":457480,"text":"have tended to focus on things\nlike conditional transfers,"},{"time":460960,"text":"where we pay and reward people\nfor doing the things"},{"time":464000,"text":"that we actually think\ncan help enhance economic growth."},{"time":467480,"text":"For example,"},{"time":468720,"text":"sending children to school,"},{"time":470360,"text":"parents could earn money for that,"},{"time":472600,"text":"or getting their children\ninoculated or immunized,"},{"time":476000,"text":"parents could get paid for doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478360,"text":"Now, quite apart from the debate"},{"time":480480,"text":"on whether or not\nwe should be paying people"},{"time":482800,"text":"to do what we think they should do anyway,"},{"time":485520,"text":"the fact of the matter\nis that pay for performance"},{"time":488720,"text":"has actually yielded some positive results"},{"time":491160,"text":"in places like Mexico,"},{"time":492880,"text":"in Brazil"},{"time":494160,"text":"and also in pilot programs in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497520,"text":"But there are also benefits"},{"time":499040,"text":"and significant changes underway\non left-leaning policies."},{"time":503880,"text":"Arguments that government should\nexpand its role and responsibility"},{"time":508160,"text":"so that it's not so narrowly defined"},{"time":510400,"text":"and that government should be\nmuch more of an arbiter"},{"time":512919,"text":"of the factors of production"},{"time":514320,"text":"have become commonplace\nwith the success of China."},{"time":517400,"text":"But also we've started to have debates"},{"time":519720,"text":"about how the role of the private sector"},{"time":522000,"text":"should move away\nfrom just being a profit motive"},{"time":524600,"text":"and really be more engaged\nin the delivery of social programs."},{"time":528120,"text":"Things like the corporate\nsocial responsibility programs,"},{"time":531360,"text":"albeit small in scale,"},{"time":533360,"text":"are moving in that right direction."},{"time":535960,"text":"Of course, left-leaning policies\nhave also tended to blur the lines"},{"time":541200,"text":"between government,\nNGOs and private sector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544800,"text":"Two very good examples of this\nare the 19th-century United States,"},{"time":548800,"text":"when the infrastructure rollout"},{"time":550440,"text":"was really about\npublic-private partnerships."},{"time":553560,"text":"More recently, of course,"},{"time":555000,"text":"the advent of the Internet\nhas also proven to the world"},{"time":558640,"text":"that public and private can work together\nfor the betterment of society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564240,"text":"My fundamental message to you is this:"},{"time":567320,"text":"We cannot continue to try and solve\nthe world economic growth challenges"},{"time":572760,"text":"by being dogmatic\nand being unnecessarily ideological."},{"time":577800,"text":"In order to create sustainable,\nlong-term economic growth"},{"time":581640,"text":"and solve the challenges and social ills\nthat continue to plague the world today,"},{"time":585960,"text":"we're going to have to be\nmore broad-minded"},{"time":588280,"text":"about what might work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590280,"text":"Ultimately,"},{"time":591880,"text":"we have to recognize\nthat ideology is the enemy of growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603160,"text":"Bruno Giussani: I want to ask\na couple of questions, Dambisa,"},{"time":606080,"text":"because one could react\nto your last sentence"},{"time":608240,"text":"by saying growth is also an ideology,"},{"time":610080,"text":"it's possibly the dominant\nideology of our times."},{"time":612440,"text":"What do you say\nto those who react that way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":614560,"text":"DM: Well, I think that that's\ncompletely legitimate,"},{"time":617040,"text":"and I think that we're already\nhaving that discussion."},{"time":619640,"text":"There's a lot of work\ngoing on around happiness"},{"time":621880,"text":"and other metrics being used\nfor measuring people's success"},{"time":625400,"text":"and improvements in living standards."},{"time":627240,"text":"And so I think that we should be open"},{"time":629320,"text":"to what could deliver improvements\nin people's living standards"},{"time":632320,"text":"and continue to reduce\npoverty around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634600,"text":"BG: So you're basically pleading\nfor rehabilitating growth,"},{"time":637440,"text":"but the only way for that happen"},{"time":639040,"text":"without compromising\nthe capacity of the earth,"},{"time":641400,"text":"to take us on a long journey,"},{"time":642960,"text":"is for economic growth"},{"time":644640,"text":"somehow to decouple\nfrom the underlying use of resources."},{"time":647360,"text":"Do you see that happening?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648680,"text":"DM: Well, I think that I'm more optimistic\nabout human ability and ingenuity."},{"time":653240,"text":"I think if we start to constrain ourselves"},{"time":655440,"text":"using the finite, scarce\nand depleting resources"},{"time":658520,"text":"that we know today,"},{"time":659800,"text":"we could get quite negative"},{"time":661160,"text":"and quite concerned\nabout the way the world is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663400,"text":"However, we've seen the Club of Rome,"},{"time":665720,"text":"we've seen previous claims"},{"time":668160,"text":"that the world would be\nrunning out of resources,"},{"time":670520,"text":"and it's not to argue\nthat those things are not valid."},{"time":673120,"text":"But I think, with ingenuity\nwe could see desalination,"},{"time":675800,"text":"I think we could reinvest in energy,"},{"time":677760,"text":"so that we can actually\nget better outcomes."},{"time":679920,"text":"And so in that sense,"},{"time":681160,"text":"I'm much more optimistic\nabout what humans can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683560,"text":"BG: The thing that strikes me"},{"time":685000,"text":"about your proposals\nfor rehabilitating growth"},{"time":688400,"text":"and taking a different direction"},{"time":690040,"text":"is that you're kind of suggesting\nto fix capitalism with more capitalism --"},{"time":695120,"text":"with putting a price tag\non good behavior as incentive"},{"time":698760,"text":"or developing a bigger role\nfor business in social issues."},{"time":702960,"text":"Is that what you're suggesting?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704480,"text":"DM: I'm suggesting\nwe have to be open-minded."},{"time":706640,"text":"I think it is absolutely the case"},{"time":708880,"text":"that traditional models of economic growth"},{"time":711360,"text":"are not working the way\nwe would like them to."},{"time":713800,"text":"And I think it's no accident"},{"time":715720,"text":"that today the largest\neconomy in the world, the United States,"},{"time":719040,"text":"has democracy,"},{"time":720360,"text":"liberal democracy,\nas it's core political stance"},{"time":723480,"text":"and it has free market capitalism --"},{"time":725680,"text":"to the extent that it is free --"},{"time":727280,"text":"free market capitalism\nas its economic stance."},{"time":729480,"text":"The second largest economy is China."},{"time":731640,"text":"It has deprioritized democracy"},{"time":733800,"text":"and it has state capitalism,\nwhich is a completely different model."},{"time":737000,"text":"These two countries,\ncompletely different political models"},{"time":739760,"text":"and completely different economic models,"},{"time":741760,"text":"and yet they have the same\nincome inequality number"},{"time":744200,"text":"measured as a Gini coefficient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745720,"text":"I think those are the debates\nwe should have,"},{"time":747880,"text":"because it's not clear at all"},{"time":750040,"text":"what model we should be adopting,"},{"time":751880,"text":"and I think there needs to be\nmuch more discourse"},{"time":754240,"text":"and much more humility\nabout what we know and what we don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757680,"text":"BG: One last question.\nThe COP21 is going on in Paris."},{"time":761080,"text":"If you could send a tweet"},{"time":762600,"text":"to all the heads of state\nand heads of delegations there,"},{"time":765920,"text":"what would you say?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":767320,"text":"DM: Again, I would be very much\nabout being open-minded."},{"time":770000,"text":"As you're aware,"},{"time":771240,"text":"the issues around\nthe environmental concerns"},{"time":773360,"text":"have been on the agenda many times now --"},{"time":775360,"text":"in Copenhagen,\n'72 in Stockholm --"},{"time":777640,"text":"and we keep revisiting these issues"},{"time":779960,"text":"partly because there is not\na fundamental agreement,"},{"time":783560,"text":"in fact there's a schism"},{"time":784840,"text":"between what the developed\ncountries believe and want"},{"time":787600,"text":"and what emerging market countries want."},{"time":789960,"text":"Emerging market countries need\nto continue to create economic growth"},{"time":793200,"text":"so that we don't have political\nuncertainty in the those countries."},{"time":796640,"text":"Developed countries recognize"},{"time":798800,"text":"that they have a real,\nimportant responsibility"},{"time":801080,"text":"not only just to manage\ntheir CO2 emissions"},{"time":803920,"text":"and some of the degradation\nthat they're contributing to the world,"},{"time":807120,"text":"but also as trendsetters in R&amp;D."},{"time":808920,"text":"And so they have to come\nto the table as well."},{"time":811200,"text":"But in essence, it cannot be a situation"},{"time":813680,"text":"where we start ascribing policies\nto the emerging markets"},{"time":817840,"text":"without developed countries themselves"},{"time":819720,"text":"also taking quite a swipe\nat what they're doing"},{"time":822120,"text":"both in demand and supply\nin developed markets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824920,"text":"BG: Dambisa, thank you for coming to TED.\nDM: Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828040,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}